{{Infobox football biography |name = Lam Ngai Tong |image = |fullname = |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1990|01|13|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Santo António, Macau|Santo António]], Macau |height = {{height|m=1.74}} |position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] |currentclub = [[Tai Po FC|Tai Po]] |clubnumber = 28 |youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = [[Hong Kong Taoist Association The Yuen Yuen Institute No.2 Secondary School|The Yuen Yuen Institute]] |years1 = 2011–2012 |clubs1 = [[Sham Shui Po SA|Sham Shui Po]] |caps1 = 16 |goals1 = 0 |years2 = 2012–2013 |clubs2 = [[Metro Gallery FC|Yokohama FC Hong Kong]] |caps2 = 16 |goals2 = 0 |years3 = 2013–2016 |clubs3 = [[Tai Po FC|Tai Po]] |caps3 = 17 |goals3 = 0 |years4 = 2016–2018 |clubs4 = [[Sparta Rotterdam (Mutual) FC|Sparta Rotterdam Mutual]] |caps4 = 43 |goals4 = 19 |years5 = 2018– |clubs5 = [[Tai Po FC|Tai Po]] |caps5 = 0 |goals5 = 0 |nationalyears1 = |nationalteam1 = [[Hong Kong national under-15 football team|Hong Kong U15]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.upower.com.hk/article/98506-由小港腳到澳門隊-林毅東國際大舞台尋夢 |title=由小港腳到澳門隊 林毅東國際大舞台尋夢 |trans-title=From Xiaogang Jiao to the Macau National Team - Lam Ngai Tong Seeks his Dream on the International Stage |date=5 September 2017 |accessdate=8 June 2018 |work=UPower |language=Chinese}}</ref> |nationalcaps1 = |nationalgoals1 = |nationalyears2 = 2017– |nationalteam2 = [[Macau national football team|Macau]] |nationalcaps2 = 6 |nationalgoals2 = 0 |club-update = 11:44, 8 June 2018 (UTC) |nationalteam-update = 11:44, 8 June 2018 (UTC) }}
'''Lam Ngai Tong''' ({{zh|t=林毅東}}; born 13 January 1993) is a [[Macau|Macanese]]-[[Hong Kong]] professional [[association football|footballer]] who currently plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[Hong Kong Premier League]] club [[Tai Po FC|Tai Po]].
==Club career== After stints at [[Sham Shui Po SA|Sham Shui Po]] and [[Metro Gallery FC|Yokohama FC Hong Kong]], Lam moved to [[Tai Po FC|Tai Po]]. His time at Tai Po saw the club win the [[2013–14 Hong Kong Second Division League|2013–14 Hong Kong Second Division]] and [[2015–16 Hong Kong First Division League|2015–16 Hong Kong First Division]] titles. However, upon the club's promotion to the [[Hong Kong Premier League]] in 2016, Lam declined to re-sign with the club in order to continue working as a physical education teacher.<ref>{{cite web |title=港澳埠際賽 前港青林毅東披澳門戰衣 |url=http://hk.on.cc/hk/bkn/cnt/sport/20170901/bkn-20170901223544054-0901_00882_001.html |website=on.cc |accessdate=1 September 2017}} {{zh-hk icon}}</ref>
In September 2016, Lee decided to resume his career at [[Hong Kong Second Division League|Hong Kong Second Division]] club [[Sparta Rotterdam (Mutual) FC|Sparta Rotterdam Mutual]].
On 31 July 2018, Lam confirmed to the media that he would resign his teaching post in order to return to Tai Po as a full-time professional footballer.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ng |first1=Ka Kei |title=單身男人無顧忌 大埔「新兵」林毅東棄教席追夢：這是我給學生的最後一堂課 |url=https://www.upower.com.hk/article/234816-%E3%80%90%E6%B8%AF%E8%B6%85%E8%81%AF%E8%B3%BD%E3%80%91%E5%96%AE%E8%BA%AB%E7%94%B7%E4%BA%BA%E7%84%A1%E9%A1%A7%E5%BF%8C-%E5%A4%A7%E5%9F%94%E3%80%8C%E6%96%B0%E5%85%B5%E3%80%8D%E6%9E%97%E6%AF%85%E6%9D%B1 |website=Upower |accessdate=31 July 2018}} {{zh-hk icon}}</ref>
